    "text": "(b') REVISES FD1 MORTE -> Verdict B (forced, dimension-dependent). k_c is SIZE-STABLE (tail spread d2=0.052, d4=0.008 over N=350..1600 -> THEOREM, not finite-N artefact; FD1's non-robustness was an N=300 effect) and tracks the Molloy-Reed z_c (degree-CV d2=0.33, d4=1.00) plus a clustering shift. But it is DIMENSION-DEPENDENT: k_c(inf) d2=1.01 (~ER-generic 1, 1sigma) vs d4=0.67 (30sigma from 1) -> eta=(k_c-1)^2 ~ 0 in d2, ~0.11 in d4. So the causal net FORCES eta as a calculable graph percolation threshold (Molloy-Reed + clustering), NOT the free SR parameter -- but selects no UNIVERSAL eta: it inherits the dimension input (as d=3 is [EXTERNO] in DS1-3). 'Why eta/hbar don't pin' = there is no dimension-independent value to pin; the threshold is a geometric graph property. Mechanism for the scales thesis (feeds B1).",
